<P>
 Ventura Kudos to Murray, Rips for Raveling 
</P>
<P>
 Thanks to Jim Murray for pointing out such an important issue in college 
athletics ("Scholarship Should Be Real Issue," Jan. 16). The universities have 
prostituted themselves in order to receive the lucrative athletic revenue. Now 
the beat they have created is turning on them, threatening to boycott and 
reduce the take.  
</P>
<P>
 Let's stop the farce. Disassociate the teams from the universities. Call them 
the Los Angeles Trojans, Bruins, etc. Pay them as minor league teams and let 
students interested in an education take the spots currently taken up by the 
hired guns. Let the universities get back to their jobs -- educating people. 
</P>
