<HEADLINE>
<P>
VALLEY ROUNDUP; CRESCENTA VALLEY'S HAGMAN HITS 13 THREE-POINT SHOTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Sarah Hagman had another record-setting night in Crescenta Valley's 87-22 
victory Friday over Arcadia. She finished with 48 points -- a school record -- 
and made a Southern Section-record 13 three-point shots. Hagman broke the 
record of 11 she shared with Brea Olinda player Nicole Erickson. Hagman had 11 
last week against Hoover. 
</P>
<P>
 The senior guard attempted 26 three-point shots. Hagman has made 97 threes to 
date and is shooting better than 40% from that range. Crescenta Valley improved 
to 15-4. 
</P>
<P>
 Other girls' games -- Trisha Palmquist scored a career-high 22 points to lead 
Village Christian over Maranatha, 78-30. . . . Tina Milburn's layup with one 
minute remaining lifted Moorpark to a 35-33 Frontier League victory over 
Calabasas. BOYS' BASKETBALL 
</P>
<P>
 Paraclete 68, Desert 63 -- Reserve forward Steve Dombrowski had 28 points for 
the Spirits (7-9, 4-2) and tied a school record with six three-point baskets in 
a High Desert League game. 
</P>
<P>
