<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY COLLEGE ROUNDUP; TWO RESERVES LEAD SADDLEBACK TO VICTORY OVER ORANGE 
COAST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By STEVE KRESAL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Saddleback started its Orange Empire Conference game at Orange Coast on Friday 
with a big hole in the middle. The Gauchos were without Eric Ambrozich, the 
starting center who is averaging 10 points and seven rebounds. 
</P>
<P>
 But by the time the game was over, Saddleback had two reserves with soaring 
confidence and a 70-52 victory. 
</P>
<P>
 The Gauchos (15-6, 5-1 in conference) remain tied with Riverside for first 
place. 
</P>
<P>
 Justin Hinsey and Jeff Rick took over in the post for Ambrozich and each made 
key contributions. Saddleback led, 30-29, at the half but outscored OCC, 23-9, 
in the first eight minutes and were never challenged the rest of the way. 
</P>
<P>
 Hinsey, making his first collegiate start, had 10 points and added seven 
rebounds. Rick had four points and four rebounds. 
</P>
<P>
 "He gave us a lift," Saddleback Coach Bill Brummel said about Hinsey. "He took 
advantage of the situation. But Jeff Rick also gave us a lift . . . Sometimes 
out of a negative something positive happens. This will make us a better team 
in the future." 
</P>
<P>
 Rick had a key rebound basket to put Saddleback ahead, 40-36, with 15 minutes 
12 seconds left. He was fouled on the shot but missed the free throw. But 
Hinsey got that rebound and went up for a lay-in and Saddleback led, 42-36. 
</P>
<P>
 Tes Whitlock continued to be impressive for Saddleback. He had a game-high 25 
points, including 16 in the second half. He had a basket then added a 
three-pointer to give Saddleback a 47-36 lead with 14:02 left. 
</P>
<P>
 Orange Coast (11-10, 1-5) missed its first 11 shots, but then made 10 of the 
next 17 in the first half.  
</P>
<P>
 But Saddleback increased the defensive pressure in the second half and OCC 
made six of 27 field-goal attempts. 
</P>
<P>
 "We've played some good defense in the last three games," Brummel said. "It's 
been our salvation." STEVE KRESAL 
</P>
</TEXT>
