COLLEGE ROUNDUP; CHAPMAN MEN'S TEAM, MISSING SEVEN PLAYERS, WINS ANYWAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Chapman, left with six players after seven were sent home for violations of 
team rules, defeated Dominican College, 80-73, in a nonconference men's 
basketball game Friday in San Francisco. 
</P>
<P>
 Stephan Mumaw and Tony Gonzalez, the only starters available, scored 22 and 19 
points for Chapman (10-6). 
</P>
<P>
 Coach Mike Bokosky sent starters Greg Reynolds, Umahl Anderson and Aaron 
Cornell and reserves Adam Dzierznski, Egar Diaz, Steve Van Horn and Rod Summers 
home in a van two days early. The college would not announce the infractions. 
</P>
<P>
 Brian Wood scored 16 and Toby Curto 13 for Chapman, which plays Menlo tonight. 
Dominican is 2-14. 
