<P>
ROSEANNE RUBBISH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Recently Liz Smith published part of an interview with Roseanne Arnold that 
appears in Vanity Fair ("Roseanne Goes on the Record," Jan. 4).I was appalled 
and sick by the time I finished. To irresponsibly say that any child who is 
abused has a right to kill his parents, no questions asked, opens up a lot of 
possibilities for children who feel that abuse can include not getting their 
own way -- Mom and Dad won't get you that car or clothes, so blow them away. 
Sound familiar? 
</P>
<P>
 I refuse to watch "Roseanne" anymore. I threw my new copy of Vanity Fair out 
as soon as I saw her on the cover. 
</P>
<P>
 SUSAN M. TODHUNTER 
