<HEADLINE>
<P>
'BLINK'S' APPEAL AT FEST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Reading Kent Black's opening paragraph as to the "sparse crowd" gathered to 
see the movie "Blink" at the closing-night ceremonies of the Palm Springs 
International Film Festival ("U.S. Films Not So Popular at Palm Springs 
Festival," Jan. 18), readers would believe that because it was an American film 
it had no appeal to festival-goers.What Black fails to mention is that the 
screening was a fund-raiser and priced at $35 a ticket, perhaps a prohibitive 
price for many. When "Blink" was shown the next afternoon at regular festival 
prices, the same theater was filled to capacity. I know, I was there and 
enjoyed the thriller! 
</P>
<P>
 STEVE SIPORIN 
