<HEADLINE>
<P>
PLAYING WITH FURNITURE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 After reading "Women at Top in Music" (Jan. 15), I find it difficult to 
believe that JoAnn Falletta would use the word credenza (def., a buffet or 
sideboard, especially one without legs) in reference to music.As a harpist 
whose career has led me to commission, perform and record numerous works by 
women composers, I know their harp music could not be characterized as 
"gentle." Their harp works are all "very strong and very powerful." And if they 
were "full of harp credenzas," just imagine the power and strength of all that 
heavy furniture on the stage! 
</P>
