ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: COUNTYWIDE; AGENCY SEEKS AID FOR QUAKE VICTIMS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JON NALICK 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Salvation Army is seeking donations of cash and essential commodities to 
help victims of the Northridge earthquake, spokesman Lee Lescano said. 
</P>
<P>
 Donations of prepackaged foods, diapers, new blankets, sleeping bags, water 
and cash should be marked "Northridge Earthquake," and sent to: Salvation Army, 
Orange County Administration, 1710 W. Edinger Ave., Santa Ana, Calif. 92704. 
</P>
<P>
 The organization is also preparing to distribute tents as well as personal 
care and household cleaning kits. 
</P>
<P>
 Anyone wishing to donate clothing and household goods may do so at the 
agency's Hospitality House, 818 E. 3rd St., Santa Ana, or the main warehouse at 
1300 S. Lewis St. in Anaheim. 
</P>
<P>
 For more information on earthquake relief efforts or to make a donation, call 
(714) 546-7880. Credit card donations may be made by calling (800) 725-9005. 
JON NALICK 
</P>
