<HEADLINE>
<P>
EARTHQUAKE: THE LONG ROAD BACK; PARTIAL LISTING OF DEATHS RELATED TO MONDAY'S 
QUAKE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Los Angeles County Coroner's office said Friday that 55 deaths are 
currently reported as being earthquake related, but the cause of many of the 
deaths will remain pending until full autopsies are completed and each case is 
reviewed. 
</P>
<P>
 Here are names of some of those who died. 
</P>
<P>
 Those who died in the collapse of the Northridge Meadows apartment building: 
</P>
<P>
 Angeline (Ann) Cerone, 80; Sharon Englar, 58; Phil Englar, 62; Darla Raye 
Enos, 43; Pil Soon Lee, 46; Hwon Lee, 14; Cecilia Pressman, 72; David Pressman, 
72; Bea Reskin, 71; Jaime Reyes, 19; Karol Runnings, 48; Manuel D. Sandoval, 
