<HEADLINE>
<P>
18-YEAR-OLD SHOT IN DRIVE-BY DIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 An 18-year-old man died Thursday night from injuries he suffered in a drive-by 
shooting that police said was gang-related. 
</P>
<P>
 Benjamin Silva Torivio of Santa Ana died at Western Medical Center-Santa Ana, 
said Police Sgt. Dick Faust. Police have no suspects in the shooting, which is 
being investigated as gang-related, Faust said. 
</P>
<P>
 Torivio and a friend were walking on East Vance Street on Wednesday when a 
small truck passed them, police said. A short distance away, the truck stopped 
and a passenger got out and fired a handgun three times in the direction of 
Torivio and his friend, police said. One of the shots hit Torivio in the head. 
</P>
