<HEADLINE>
<P>
MOTEL ROOMS OFFERED TO QUAKE VICTIMS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Motel owners in South Gate are making more than 100 rooms available free of 
charge to families left homeless by the earthquake. 
</P>
<P>
 The rooms will be available to families for up to a week, said Sam Patidar, 
treasurer of the South Gate Motel Owners Assn. 
</P>
<P>
 The group took the action after City Councilman Albert Robles got the idea. 
</P>
<P>
 "If motel owners throughout the city can donate vacant rooms . . . it could go 
a long way toward solving the housing problems from the earthquake," Robles 
said. "We need to work together to get people out of their cars and parks and 
into some shelter." 
</P>
</TEXT>
