<HEADLINE>
<P>
4 ARRESTED IN SLAYING OF WHITTIER MAN; CRIME: THE SUSPECTS, ALLEGEDLY CONNECTED 
TO AN OXNARD GANG, ARE ACCUSED IN A DECEMBER SHOOTING AT A VENTURA MOTEL. 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JULIE FIELDS, SPECIAL TO THE TIMES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Ventura police on Friday arrested three men and a woman in connection with the 
fatal shooting of a 21-year-old Whittier man at a Ventura motel last month, 
authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Police said the four suspects -- all alleged members or associates of the same 
Oxnard gang -- were at the Motel 6 on Johnson Drive in Ventura the night Paul 
Martinez was gunned down on the second-story balcony. 
</P>
<P>
 "They're all believed to have been acting in concert at the time of the 
shooting," Ventura Police Lt. Steve Bowman said. 
</P>
<P>
 The arrests came after more than 150 police officers swooped down on 13 homes 
in Oxnard and Port Hueneme before dawn Friday, looking for evidence in the Dec. 
18 killing. Police executed search warrants at a dozen of the homes and 
conducted a probation search at one other starting at 4:30 a.m. 
</P>
<P>
 Police confiscated several firearms and clubs and impounded two vehicles 
believed to have been at the scene of the shooting. 
</P>
<P>
 Bowman said he did not know whether detectives found the gun used to kill 
Martinez. 
</P>
<P>
 After hours of questioning more than a half dozen suspects, police arrested 
Shaun Bolo, 20, and his brother, Willard, 23, both of Oxnard and Steven 
Hidalgo, 20, and Naomi Honohan, 19, both of Port Hueneme. 
</P>
<P>
 Investigators booked all four into Ventura County Jail on suspicion of murder. 
They were being held late Friday in lieu of $250,000 bail. They are scheduled 
to appear in Ventura County Municipal Court on Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
 A 23-year-old Oxnard man also was arrested on outstanding warrants, and a 
16-year-old male was taken to Juvenile Hall on suspicion of possessing a stolen 
handgun and methamphetamine. 
</P>
<P>
 Sgt. Bob Anderson, who is in charge of the case, could not be reached for 
comment Friday. But earlier, he described the killing as an apparently random 
act of violence involving gang members. 
</P>
<P>
 "It's apparent a gun was pulled out at a moment's notice, totally unplanned," 
he said. "One group of people from one city decided to shoot at people from 
another city." 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 "The basic motive behind this crime was that there was someone at the hotel 
from Los Angeles and someone from Oxnard didn't like it," Anderson said. 
</P>
<P>
 Since beginning their investigation, detectives have focused on a group of 
people from Oxnard who were having a party in a room at the motel shortly 
before the shooting. Police have said they do not believe Martinez knew any of 
the suspects. 
</P>
<P>
 The night of the shooting, Martinez had driven to Santa Paula with a friend, 
Gerald Razo, to meet one of Razo's army buddies. But when they got to Santa 
Paula, someone suggested the party move to the Motel 6 on Johnson Drive. 
</P>
<P>
 Martinez worked as a shoe salesman and had a 2-week-old daughter when he was 
killed. 
</P>
<P>
 "He just wanted to have a better life for his girlfriend and his baby," Razo 
said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
