<HEADLINE>
<P>
VALLEY DIGEST; NORTHRIDGE'S MICELLI ATTENDING TO FUNERAL PLANS FOR HIS FATHER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MIKE HISERMAN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 While most Cal State Northridge basketball players were finding other places 
to live Friday in the aftermath of Monday's 6.6 earthquake, center Peter 
Micelli was helping with funeral arrangements for his father. 
</P>
<P>
 Nicholas Micelli, 50, was found dead in a Camarillo motel room Thursday, the 
victim of an apparent heart attack.A 10 a.m. burial Mass will be held Monday at 
Good Shepard Catholic Church in Beverly Hills. 
</P>
<P>
 Micelli, a prominent lawyer, was among the basketball team's most enthusiastic 
supporters, attending all of the Matadors' games. 
</P>
<P>
 "My heart goes out to Peter and his family," Northridge Coach Pete Cassidy 
said. "It is crushing to all of us. He was close to the kids and supported 
Peter tremendously. 
</P>
<P>
 "He was an extremely giving man. He always looked to help young people and 
people who weren't as fortunate as he was." 
</P>
<P>
 Micelli was on his way to San Francisco to work on a case when he stopped at 
the motel Wednesday night because he was not feeling well, Northridge spokesman 
Barry Smith said. Earlier in the day he stopped at Peter's rented Northridge 
home to drop off food and supplies for students who were staying there after 
being displaced by the earthquake. 
</P>
<P>
 Micelli is survived by his wife, Frances, Peter and daughters Pauline and 
Maria. MIKE HISERMAN 
</P>
