<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY: TELECOMMUNICATIONS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 TCI Delays Buying Converter Boxes: The nation's largest cable TV company said 
it will delay for a year the purchase of 1 million set-top boxes that turn a TV 
into a two-way communications device.The delay is not significant in its 
development of more powerful communications networks, Tele-Communications Inc. 
said. But it shows the technical difficulties in developing even the simplest 
of advanced communications products, video on demand. Set-top boxes are 
changing from simply handling numerous cable channels to understanding the 
digital language of computers and processing programs, data services and phone 
calls. In time, the advanced features in such a box will be incorporated into 
TVs. 
</P>
