<HEADLINE>
<P>
WEEKEND TV; EARTHQUAKE UPDATES FILL THE SCHEDULE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By N.F. MENDOZA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 This weekend, several national and local programs will focus on Monday's 
Northridge earthquake and relief for its victims. 
</P>
<P>
 Here's a list of shows with earthquake reports: 
</P>
<P>
 Today: "Today" features the Southern California earthquake, as well as a look 
at new houseware items; a Lake Placid, N.Y., luge camp and author Michael 
Crichton ("Disclosure"), 6 a.m. (4)(39); 7 a.m. (36). 
</P>
<P>
 Gov. Pete Wilson, Sen. Barbara Boxer (D-Calif.) and County Supervisor Yvonne 
Brathwaite Burke discuss the rebuilding after Monday's temblor on "Newsmaker 
Saturday," 10:30 a.m. CNN. 
</P>
<P>
 The earthquake is discussed on "Larry King Weekend," 6 p.m., CNN. 
</P>
<P>
 Earthquake preparedness in other U.S. cities is the topic on "The Crusaders," 
7 p.m. (4). 
</P>
<P>
 "Front Page" presents an update on the Northridge earthquake, 9 p.m. (11)(6). 
</P>
<P>
 Sunday: "Sunday Today" looks at the Northridge earthquake. Also featured is a 
report on Golden Globe winners, 6 a.m. (4)(39); 7 a.m. (36). 
</P>
<P>
 "Sunday Morning" features earthquake updates, as well as Reps. Cynthia 
McKinney (D-Ga.) and Newt Gingrich (R-Ga.) discuss issues awaiting Congress; 
composers Jerry Bock, Sheldon Harnick; Nebraska farm families and preserving 
historical Las Vegas sites, "The Critic," 7:30 a.m. (2); 8 a.m. (8). 
</P>
<P>
 An update on the earthquake with Mayor Richard Riordan is featured on "This 
Week With David Brinkley," 11:30 a.m. (7)(3), 10 a.m. (10). . . . 
</P>
<P>
 The quake and how victims can get help is the topic on "L.A. Extra," 10:30 
a.m. (7). 
</P>
<P>
 Helping children deal with earthquakes is the subject of "Midday Sunday," 11 
a.m. (11). N.F. MENDOZA 
</P>
